<td style="vertical-align:inherit;padding:0"></td>
</tr>
</table>
<div class="thumbcaption">Position before 67.Bd5</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>This position was reached in a game from the 1965 <a href="/wiki/Candidates_Tournament" title="Candidates Tournament">Candidates Tournament</a> between <a href="/wiki/Lajos_Portisch" title="Lajos Portisch">Lajos Portisch</a> and former <a href="/wiki/World_Chess_Champion" class="mw-redirect" title="World Chess Champion">World Champion</a> <a href="/wiki/Mikhail_Tal" title="Mikhail Tal">Mikhail Tal</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-12" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-12">[12]</a></sup> White must defend accurately and utilize <a href="/wiki/Zugzwang#Reciprocal_zugzwang" title="Zugzwang">reciprocal zugzwang</a>. Often he has only one or two moves that avoid a losing position. Black was unable to make any progress and the game was drawn on move 83 (<a href="#CITEREFNunn1995">Nunn 1995</a>:169).</p>
<div style="clear:both;"></div>
